<h4 id=3D"implementation-considerations">Implementation Considerations<a cl=
ass=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://benavlabs.github.io/crudadmin/usage/comm=
on-patterns/#implementation-considerations" title=3D"Permanent link">=C2=B6=
</a></h4>
<p>When using this workaround pattern:</p>
<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>=E2=9C=85 Simple to implement and understand</li>
<li>=E2=9C=85 Complete separation between different access levels</li>
<li>=E2=9C=85 Different URLs for different roles (<code>/superadmin</code>,=
 <code>/content</code>, <code>/service</code>)</li>
<li>=E2=9C=85 Independent authentication for each role</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>=E2=9D=8C Requires separate admin instances and maintenance</li>
<li>=E2=9D=8C No shared user session across different admin interfaces</li>
<li>=E2=9D=8C Duplicate configuration and setup code</li>
<li>=E2=9D=8C Users need separate credentials for different admin areas</li=
>
</ul>
<p><strong>Future RBAC Features:</strong></p>
<p>When CRUDAdmin adds native role-based access control, you'll be able to:=
</p>
<ul>
<li>Define roles and permissions in a single admin instance</li>
<li>Control model visibility and actions per user role</li>
<li>Share sessions across the same admin interface</li>
<li>Dynamically show/hide features based on user permissions</li>
</ul>
